  • Method Details

    • partSearchHandler

      public void partSearchHandler()
      This method searches for parts in the all parts table. If a part is found it add that part to the search results. If no part is found a message pops up stating no results found. If no part is found the search field is reset. Search Results are added into the all parts table.

    • initialize

      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      This is the initialize method. This runs first. This sets up the tables and puts the selected product information into the text fields.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
      Parameters:
      url - url.
      resourceBundle - rb.

    • modifyProductFormAddClick

      public void modifyProductFormAddClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Takes the selected part from the all parts table and associates it with the product. This also displays it in the associated parts table.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - Add button clicked.

    • modifyProductFormRAPClick

      public void modifyProductFormRAPClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Used to remove an associated part from a product. Error Message pops up if not part is selected. Confirmation box pops up before part is deleted. Removes associated part from a product and associated part table.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - Remove Associated Part button clicked.

    • modifyProductFormSaveClick

      public void modifyProductFormSaveClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Saves the modifications to the selected product. Contains error handling for the modify product form. Returns user to the main screen if product is modified successfully.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - Save Button Clicked.

    • modifyProductFormCancelClick

      public void modifyProductFormCancelClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Cancels the modifications to the product. Confirmation box appears beofre exit. Returns the user to the main screen after confirmation.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - Cancel Button Clicked.
      Throws:
      IOException - exception.

    • partSearchKeyPress

      public void partSearchKeyPress(javafx.scene.input.KeyEvent keyEvent)
      This method calls the search handler when a key is pressed within the search text field. Resets the table to include all parts if the search field is empty.
      Parameters:
      keyEvent - Key pressed within search text field.
